    <info>
        <title>Fagaras Mountains</title>
    </info>
    <section>
        <title>Introduction</title>
        <para>Fagaras mountains, known as Transylvanian Alps, are the highest mountains of the <link
                xlink:href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Southern_Carpathians">Southern
                Carpathians</link>, in Romania. The highest peaks are:<itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para><emphasis role="italic"><link
                                xlink:href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moldoveanu_Peak-broken"
                                >Moldoveanu</link></emphasis> 2,544 m</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para><emphasis role="italic"><link
                                xlink:href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Negoiu"
                            >Negoiu</link></emphasis> 2,535 m</para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist></para>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Mountain Lakes</title>
        <para>Mountain lakes, or tarns, are truly jewels of nature and they are said to be the
            pearls of mountains.</para>
        <section audience="expert" xml:id="caltun">
            <title>Călţun</title>
            <para>Lake Caltun is situated at an altitude of 2135 m, at the foot of the Caltun peak
                (2510 m).</para>
            <para><inlinemediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="images/lake.jpeg"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </inlinemediaobject></para>
        </section>
        <section audience="novice">
            <title>Bâlea</title>
            <para>The biggest lake in the Făgăraş Mountains, part of a crowded tourist resort,
                located in the middle part of the main ridge by the Transfăgărăşan Road. Altitude
                2030.</para>
            <para><inlinemediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata
                            fileref="images/balea-lac-1747851_640.jpg"
                            scale="50"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </inlinemediaobject></para>
            <para>If you visit it, go see <link linkend="caltun">Lake Caltun</link> as well.</para>
        </section>
    </section>
